com.destroystokyo.paper.loottable

Interface Lootable

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    Chest, Dispenser, Hopper, LootableBlockInventory, LootableEntityInventory, LootableInventory, ShulkerBox

    public interface Lootable
    Defines an object that has a Loot Table and seed associated with it. How the Loot Table and seed are used may vary based on Minecraft Versions and what type of object is using the Loot Table

    • Method Summary

    • Method Detail

      • getLootTableName

        String getLootTableName()
        Gets the name of the Loot Table to be used in the World Folder
        Returns:
        The name, or null if no loot table exists

      • hasLootTable

        default boolean hasLootTable()
        Returns whether or not this object has a Loot Table
        Returns:
        Has a loot table

      • setLootTable

        default String setLootTable(String name)
        Sets the name of the Loot Table to be used in the World Folder Will use a random seed (0)
        Parameters:
        name - name in either foo or minecraft:foo format
        Returns:
        The previous Loot Table before the change

      • setLootTable

        String setLootTable(String name,
                    long seed)
        Sets the name of the Loot Table to be used in the World Folder Uses supplied Seed
        Parameters:
        name - name in either foo or minecraft:foo format
        seed - seed for the loot table. If 0, seed will be random
        Returns:
        The previous Loot Table before the change

      • getLootTableSeed

        long getLootTableSeed()
        Gets the current seed associated to the Loot Table on this object
        Returns:
        The seed, or 0 for random

      • setLootTableSeed

        default long setLootTableSeed(long seed)
        Changes the current seed associated with the Loot Table on this object. The seed will have no affect if this object does not have a Loot Table associated with it.
        Parameters:
        seed - The seed to use, or 0 for random
        Returns:
        The previous seed
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - If called when this object does not have a loot table

      • clearLootTable

        void clearLootTable()
        Clears the associated Loot Table to this object
